Boil a half-full #kettle{}.

Pour the @boiled water for the rice{300%ml} into a large #saucepan{} with
@salt{1/4%tsp} on high heat. Add the @Basmati Rice{150%g} and cook for
~{10-12%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #sieve{} and pop back in the pan. Cover with a lid and
leave to the side until ready to serve.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a
#garlic press{}).

Heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a large #frying pan{} on medium heat.

Once hot, add the @tikka masala paste{75%g} and garlic. Fry until fragrant,
~{1%minute}.

Add the @diced British chicken breast{260%g}, @mango chutney{40%g},
@coconut milk{200%ml}, @chicken stock paste{10%g}, and @water for the sauce{75%ml}
to the pan.

Stir together and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Bring to the boil, then lower the heat and simmer until the chicken is cooked
and the sauce has thickened, ~{10-12%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its
> packaging. It's cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

When your curry chicken is cooked through, stir through the @peas{120%g} until
piping hot, ~{1%minute}.

Taste your chicken tikka masala and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if
needed.

Fluff up the rice with a #fork{}.

Share the rice between your #bowls{}.

Top with the mango and coconut chicken curry.

Enjoy!